description: Learned borrowing from Latin meātus (“a going, passing; a way, path, passage”).

entries.meaning: (anatomy) A tubular opening or passage leading to the interior of the body.
examples: The urinary meatus is the opening of the urethra, situated on the glans penis in males, and in the vulva in females.

entries.meaning: (anatomy) Ellipsis of acoustic meatus, the passage leading into the ear.
